Greenpeace is seeking to raise  awareness of the need to protect ancient forests in Indonesia's  Papua, where a virtual "lost world" of new species was discovered  last year, an activist said Tuesday.
Conservationists in Sri Lanka, the  world's top spot for frogs, have discovered 35 new species of the  amphibians -- only to find that another 19 species have died out.
After six-and-a-half years of mending  broken legs and treating disease, Australia's only frog hospital is  closing its doors due to a lack of funding.
